To determine the effects of packaging on the commercial life of olive oil several studies have been carried out, and different containers such as clear and dark bottles, polyethylene and tin containers have been taken into consideration (
 Pristouri et al., 2010; 
 Gargouri et al., 2015). In most cases, storage stability of oils in tin or stainless containers and in dark glass was the highest (
 Dabbou et al., 2011; 
 Gargouri et al., 2015). Besides the type of packaging, also storage temperature plays a fundamental role; 
 Pristouri et al. (2010) observed that the shelf life of oil was improved in dark colored containers stored in the dark at temperatures lower than 22 °C.
